      <div class="description">
  
    
      <p>WIN is a pilot wireless broadband network for fast internet access at the 3.5 GHz licensed frequency band funded by the IST Program of the European Union Commission.  WIN is the first such near commercial size cellular wireless network ever operated at the 3.5 GHz frequency band in Greece.  The WIN network consists of two cells covering a large portion, approximately 35, of the Athens bay.
